						<div class="postbody">Hi, In my single screen game I wanted to have multiple, independently moving platforms, is it possible to split more than two times the screen on a NROM project, using only Sprite0 and Audio Sample Channel? I wanted the platforms to work more or less like this old arcade game: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JVS9YRkg-uw">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JVS9YRkg-uw</a><!-- m --><br /><br />If it's not possible, is there any alternatives? All moving sprites are 16x16 but I might change it to 16x24, and all I can think of is:<br /><br />1. Use black sprites and move them to simulate movement in the platform (as smooth as scrolling, but at least 3 or 4 sprites would be used per hole, and I would like to be able to place at least two holes per platform without having crazy flicker when the main character goes through them)<br /><br />2. Limit the scrolling to the platform that the player is currently (boring! and I'm not sure if I could make a fun, challenging game with stationary platforms with my current design)<br /><br />3. No platform scrolling, redesign of the game ( <img src="./images/smilies/icon_sad.gif" alt=":(" title="Sad" /> )<br /><br />Any ideas?</div>

