						<div class="postbody">I didn't know you'd reply so fast, but I thought of two more after rewatching the video. If it's fine to interpret as a moving hole in a static floor or wall, as seen in <em>Kaos</em> and <em>Jawbreaker</em>, this can be done by adding and removing floor sections in the background. This opens two more methods:<br /><br />6. The method of Chocolate Ghost house in <em>Super Mario World</em>. Use one sprite for the left and right side of each hole. This requires two sprites per hole, one for each side, which might start to screw you when three holes are on one line.<br /><br />7. Eight different tiles for different amounts missing from the right side of a tile, and eight more for the left.</div>

