			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">With MMC3, there are a few games with many scroll splits, like Bucky O'Hare: <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=g2BxMv0NalI#t=2m06s" class="postlink">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=g2BxMv0NalI#t=2m06s</a><br /><br />If you're trying to use sprite 0 hit and/or DPCM IRQ, I expect jitter might make it difficult to do more than few lines, since the jitter error will compound for each additional line. (I'm not sure whether other IRQs would have this problem. The MMC3 I think would be stable as long as you acknowledge before the next scanline is counted.)<br /><br />The other option is sprite 0 to hit the first one, and then some carefully made NOP loops to time the splits. This is more stable (the only jitter will be from sprite 0 hit, no compounds), but you can't do it for the whole screen because you need to leave some time for game logic to run. Also, DPCM should be avoided here since it introduces jitter.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
