					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I like the idea of using sprites to make tile rewrites smoother, I would have 2x sprites per hole, so at worst case I could have 2 holes x 2 Sprites + Character x 2 Sprites + Enemy x 2 Sprites = 8 sprites/scanline. I could have 3 holes, but since it would be hard to have the enemy AND the character to be at the same line traversing holes I could flicker the enemy with no problem. This is the simplest approach and I rather not do more tricky stuff, specially on my first project  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" /> <br /><br />Maybe I could use 6 tiles to represent the edges of the hole moving but I'll see if I have room to spare, it's a NROM game, after all.<br /><br />Thanks a lot!  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" /></div>

